A father and son duo were among three killed in a road crash involving two motorbikes that collided head on in the Kombani area on the Mombasa-Lunga Lunga road. According to reports, the two bikes collided and burst into flames with the father and son duo sustaining serious burns in the wee hours of Thursday. Reports say the man was on the motorbike with his son and his wife during the accident that also killed a businessman who was on the second bike. According to police officers, the woman who lost her husband and her son in the accident and the rider of the second bike are receiving medical care at the Mswambweni County Referral Hospital. The bodies of the deceased were removed to the Mswambweni County Referral Hospital mortuary. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam